[thinking] I’m considering that the static initialization of FrameworkLogger might occur before any reference to the stub classes. The test class can reference Level.class and others, but I need to ensure that when FrameworkLogger first loads, Class.forName will correctly find those stubs. 
[thinking] 
[thinking] To achieve this, I think I need to implement a stub for Level that includes the toLevel method to record the requested names. This feels crucial for ensuring everything links up correctly.
[thinking] 
[thinking] **Checking test dependencies**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm wondering if the test runtime classpath could include log4j. I need to check dependencies closely. There's a possibility that our test source class, org.apache.logging.log4j.Logger, might conflict if it's part of the transitive dependencies. But if there's no actual dependency, then it should be fine. I also realize that Gradle itself isn't included on the test classpath, which simplifies things a bit.
[thinking] 
