anager in the same file as package-private top-level classes. My main concern is whether Class.getMethod only returns public methods. If a class is package-private but has a public method, I think Class.getMethod should still return it. However, invoking it from FrameworkLogger may lead to an IllegalAccessException. \\n\\nI realize that in Java, there's only one public top-level class per file, so I could make support classes public but nested. I wonder if using separate public files might be more straightforward for testing.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Implementing static initialization**\\n\\nI’m considering that the static initialization of FrameworkLogger might occur before any reference to the stub classes. The test class can reference Level.class and others, but I need to ensure that when FrameworkLogger first loads, Class.forName will correctly find those stubs. \\n\\nTo achieve this, I think I need to implement a stub for Level that includes the toLevel method to record the requested names. This feels crucial for ensuring everything links up correctly.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Checking test dependencies**\\n\\nI'm wondering if the test runtime classpath could include log4j. I need to check dependencies closely. There's a possibility that our test source class, org.apache.logging.log4j.Logger, might conflict if it's part of the transitive dependencies. But if there's no actual dependency, then it should be fine. I also realize that Gradle itself isn't included on the test classpath, which simplifies things a bit.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_xml0nv5wseUHGhypxArDUUFm|fc_05023f7eef464c290169f8d088f1348196ac944a35ddac9c99", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.hsqldb/hsqldb/2.4.1/user-code-filter.json"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2028, "output": 1435, "cacheRead": 17920, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 21383, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777913972010, "responseId": "resp_05023f7eef464c290169f8d0748c948196aae066e8114a882a"}}
